quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,53,"That is because Allah would never change a blessing He has conferred on a people until they had changed what was in themselves. Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,54,Such was the case with Pharaoh´s people and those before them. They denied their Lord´s Signs so We destroyed them for their wrong actions. We drowned Pharaoh´s people. All of them were wrongdoers
  8,55,The worst of animals in the sight of Allah are those who are kafir and do not have iman
  8,56,those with whom you make a treaty and who then break it every time. They have no taqwa
  8,57,"So if you come upon such people in war, make a harsh example of them to deter those coming after them so that hopefully they will pay heed"
  8,58,"If you fear treachery on the part of a people, revoke your treaty with them mutually. Allah does not love treacherous people"
  8,59,Do not imagine that those who are kafir have got ahead. They are quite powerless
  8,60,"Arm yourselves against them with all the firepower and cavalry you can muster, to terrify the enemies of Allah and your enemies, and others besides them whom you do not know. Allah knows them. Anything you spend in the Way of Allah will be repaid to you in full. You will not be wronged"
  8,61,"If they incline to peace, you too incline to it, and put your trust in Allah. He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing"